NEW: CHAIRMAN @RepJerryNadler STATEMENT ON JUDICIARY COMMITTEE IMPEACHMENT PROCEDURES.

 https://judiciary.house.gov/news/press-releases/chairman-nadler-statement-judiciary-committee-impeachment-procedures … pic.twitter.com/ZvYwmtMsLT
.@HouseJudiciary Committee is committed to executing its part of the House’s ongoing impeachment investigation with the highest fealty to the Constitution.

Consistent with its historic role @HouseJudiciary will operate under equally serious procedures to govern its part of the House’s ongoing impeachment inquiry. 

These procedures confer rights for the minority and President equal to those provided during Nixon & Clinton inquiries.
.@RepJerryNadler: This is a serious moment for our Nation.

The evidence collected paints the picture of a President who abused his power to press a foreign country to interfere in the 2020 election. 

The next phase will move from closed depositions to open hearings where the American people will learn about the President’s misconduct.

The resolution also establishes procedures for the transfer of evidence to the @HouseJudiciary Committee as it considers potential articles of impeachment, and it sets forth due process rights for the President and his Counsel in the Judiciary Committee proceeding.

The House impeachment inquiry has collected extensive evidence and testimony, and soon the American people will hear from witnesses in an open setting. The resolution introduced today in the House Rules Committee will provide that pathway forward.

FACT: Domestic & sexual violence incidents are often underreported. The country is begging the Senate to act. The House passed #VAWA, but @SenateMajLdr Mitch McConnell refuses to hold a vote on this vital legislation.

.@RepJerryNadler: The 14th and 15th Amendments empower us to enact laws protecting the right to vote and guaranteeing the equal protection of all citizens. I am proud to have led the @HouseJudiciary in successfully recommending this legislation to the full House.

The Shelby County decision unleashed a deluge of voter suppression laws across the nation.  #HR4 provides a much-needed restoration of those protections to finally reverse this tide of voter suppression laws.

The right to vote lies at the very core of our democracy and is foundational to the rule of law. Before the #VotingRights Act many states and localities implemented voter suppression measures aimed at African Americans and other people of color.
